FORGEZERO CLI REFERENCE
========================

SYNOPSIS
--------
fz [options] [sources...]

ForgeZero accepts a primary build entry point such as assembly, C/C++, Gloria,
a directory build, initialization, shell mode, contributor mode, or an explicit
configuration file.

CORE OPTIONS
------------
-init
    Scaffold a new project. Creates .fz.toml, .fzignore, configure.fz, and
    README.txt style scaffolding when absent.
-config <file>
    Load a specific TOML or YAML configuration file.
--set <key=value>
    Apply runtime overrides such as output, mode, profile, or flags.
-profile, -p <name>
    Select a named profile: performance, balanced, or power-saver.
-mode <auto|c|raw>
    Choose the linker strategy.
-target <triple>
    Cross-compile for a target triple.
-j <N>
    Set worker count; 0 uses the detected CPU count.
-debug
    Pass debug information to the toolchain.
-verbose
    Print each executed command.
-json
    Emit a machine-readable build report.
-watch
    Rebuild automatically when watched sources change.
-clean
    Remove build artifacts and exit.
-compile-commands
    Emit compile_commands.json for IDE integration.
-update
    Download and install the latest ForgeZero binary.
-h, --help
    Print help and exit.
-v, --version
    Print version and build metadata.

CONFIGURATION SOURCES
----------------------
ForgeZero resolves configuration in this order:
1. system config
2. user config
3. local project config
4. runtime overrides from --set

Common locations include /etc/fz.toml, ~/.config/fz/config.toml, ./.fz.toml,
and ./fz.toml.

BUILD PROFILES
--------------
performance
    Maximize build throughput with more parallelism and higher optimization.
balanced
    Default developer profile.
power-saver
    Reduce resource consumption for laptops and CI workers.

LINKING MODES
-------------
auto
    Default path; attempts the most suitable linker strategy.
c
    Force a compiler-driven link. Recommended for libc-dependent code.
raw
    Force direct linker usage for kernels, bootloaders, and freestanding
    binaries.

SUBCOMMANDS
-----------
fz pm add <repo>
    Install a package from a Git repository.
fz pm remove <name>
    Remove an installed package.
fz pm list
    List installed packages.
fz sbom
    Generate a CycloneDX SBOM.
fz audit
    Run static analysis and policy checks.
fz verify
    Verify the source tree against a BLAKE3 manifest.
fz doctor
    Run the platform and toolchain self-check.
fz bench
    Profile build phases.
fz contribute
    Generate contributor guidance.

EXIT CODES
----------
0
    Success.
1
    Build, verification, or audit failure.
2
    Invalid arguments or unreadable configuration.
